                JAMES'S STORY
        Sick Violence Extraordinary
        ---------------------------
The scene: An abandoned wood cabin somewhere in England.
The cast: James, the innocent two-year-old victim.
                Jon and Robert, the ten-year-old merciless killers.
The time: 1990something.

        ACT ONE
Robert hits James in the mouth and connects. James loses two teeth.
James hits Robert in the knee and connects. Robert's knee starts to bleed (2
pts damage).
Jon hits James in the stomach and connects. James flies backwards towards wall.
James hits the wall (back 10 pts damage).
Robert reaches for club and grabs it.
Jon jumps on James. James takes 20 pts damage to stomach. James receives a
stomach wound.
Robert hits James with club but fails, hitting Jon instead. Jon receives a back
wound (5 pts damage).
Jon gets up off James.
James gets up.

        ACT TWO
James runs madly at Jon and connects, knocking himself and Jon to the floor.
James takes 5 pts damage. James loses three teeth. Jon takes 20 pts damage. Jon
breaks a fingernail.
Robert slices James's back with his bare nails. James takes 2 pts damage.
Robert breaks a fingernail.
Robert reaches for two-handed sword and grabs it.
Robert hits James with two-handed sword, aiming directly to the head. The two-
anded sword misses James's head, denting his right shoulder instead. James's
shoulder starts to bleed (5 pts damage).
James reaches for stick and grabs it.
James pokes Robert with stick but fails, causing no damage to anyone.
Robert tries to steal James's stick but fails, resulting in James's nails
tearing open his palm (10 pts damage). James breaks two fingernails.
James drops the stick.

        ACT THREE
Jon reaches for semi-automatic pistol but fails, dropping it to the floor.
Robert reaches for semi-automatic pistol and grabs it.
James hits the semi-automatic pistol and connects, causing Robert to drop the
semi-automatic pistol and receive 1 pts damage to the right hand.
Jon reaches for semi-automatic pistol and grabs it.
Jon fires semi-automatic pistol at James's heart. The bullet hits James's
heart, causing it to explode. James receives major heart failure (50 pts
damage). James is coated with blood. Robert is coated with blood.

        ACT FOUR
Robert hits James with two-handed sword, aiming directly to the neck. The two-
anded sword connects with James's neck, tearing James's head off. James's head
falls to the floor. James receives a crack on the skull (40 pts damage). James
is dead.
Jon kicks James's head. The head flies towards a wall. The head hits the wall
and shatters. The wall is coated with blood.
Jon runs at James's head and slips over James's brain. Jon falls down, knocking
Robert down. Jon takes 10 pts damage to the back. Robert takes 20 pts damage to
the back.
Jon gets up off Robert.
Robert gets up.
Robert reaches for anvil but fails, causing it to drop on James's corpse. The
anvil hits James's corpse, shattering its ribcage. The anvil is coated with
blood. The floor is coated with blood.
Jon ends fighting, victorious.
Robert ends fighting, victorious.

        END RESULTS:
        James : condition: dead   combat points: 0
        Jon   : condition: alive  combat points: 100
        Robert: condition: alive  combat points: 100
